DormChef Release Notes
======================

## Version 2.0.0
Release Date: April 6, 2024
Status: Production Ready ✅

### New Features

#### 1. Multi-Appliance Support
- Generate recipes using multiple kitchen appliances simultaneously
- API now accepts `appliance_ids` array instead of single `appliance` string
- Recipes stored with many-to-many relationship to appliances
- LLM considers all selected appliances in recipe generation

#### 2. Custom Appliances Management
- Users can add custom kitchen appliances with name and description
- Full CRUD API endpoints for appliance management:
  - GET /api/appliances - List all appliances
  - POST /api/appliances - Create custom appliance
  - PUT /api/appliances/{id} - Update appliance
  - DELETE /api/appliances/{id} - Delete appliance
- Built-in appliances protected (cannot be edited/deleted)
- Real-time validation (no duplicate names allowed)
- Admin UI for managing appliances with modals

#### 3. Dark Mode / Light Theme
- Theme toggle button in header (🌙/☀️)
- Persistent theme preference via localStorage
- CSS root variables for easy color switching
- Optimized color scheme for both modes

#### 4. Internationalization (i18n)
- Full support for English and Russian languages
- 100+ translated UI strings
- Language toggle button in header (🌍)
- Persistent language preference via localStorage
- Easy to extend with additional languages

#### 5. Enhanced LLM Integration
- Improved system prompt for multi-appliance scenarios
- Better recipe quality and formatting
- Handles appliance constraints more intelligently
- Fallback to mock service if API unavailable

### Improvements

- Frontend refactored with tabs for Generator and Appliances management
- Multi-select appliance interface (checkboxes instead of dropdown)
- Real-time appliance list updates
- Better error messages and user feedback
- Comprehensive test suite (30+ unit/integration tests)
- Enhanced API documentation

### Breaking Changes

**⚠️ API v1.0 → v2.0 Migration**

Old format (v1.0):
```json
POST /api/generate
{
  "ingredients": ["eggs"],
  "appliance": "microwave"
}

Response:
{
  "appliance": "microwave",
  "content": {...}
}
```

New format (v2.0):
```json
POST /api/generate
{
  "ingredients": ["eggs"],
  "appliance_ids": [1]
}

Response:
  "appliances": [
    {"id": 1, "name": "Microwave", "is_default": true, ...}
  ],
  "content": {...}
}
```

### Database Changes

- Added `Appliance` ORM model
- Created `recipe_appliances` many-to-many junction table
- Removed single `appliance` column from `Recipe` table
- Seeded 6 default appliances: Microwave, Toaster, Hot Plate, Air Fryer, Oven, Blender

### File Changes

- **backend/main.py**: Version bumped to 2.0.0, 4 new CRUD endpoints
- **backend/models.py**: Added Appliance Pydantic models, updated Recipe schemas
- **backend/database.py**: Added Appliance ORM, many-to-many relationship
- **backend/llm_service.py**: Enhanced prompts for multi-appliance support
- **backend/mock_llm_service.py**: Updated mock service for testing
- **frontend/index.html**: Complete UI refactor with tabs, modals, checkboxes
- **frontend/translations.js**: NEW - 100+ strings in EN/RU
- **backend/test_appliances.py**: NEW - 30+ test cases

### New Files

- `TESTING.md` - Comprehensive manual testing guide
- `integration_test.sh` - Automated integration test script
